org.sxb.data.redis.transaction

インタフェース PriorityOrdered

  • すべてのスーパーインタフェース:
    Ordered

    public interface PriorityOrdered
extends Ordered
    Extension of the Ordered interface, expressing a priority ordering: order values expressed by PriorityOrdered objects always apply before same order values expressed by plain Ordered objects.

    This is primarily a special-purpose interface, used for objects where it is particularly important to recognize prioritized objects first, without even obtaining the remaining objects. A typical example: prioritized post-processors in a Spring org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext.

    Note: PriorityOrdered post-processor beans are initialized in a special phase, ahead of other post-processor beans. This subtly affects their autowiring behavior: they will only be autowired against beans which do not require eager initialization for type matching.

    導入されたバージョン:
    2.5
    作成者:
    Juergen Hoeller
    関連項目:
    org.springframework.beans.factory.config.PropertyOverrideConfigurer, org.springframework.beans.factory.config.PropertyPlaceholderConfigurer
